behavioral lab stanford gsb skip to content stanford graduate school of business behavioral lab az index find people visit admissions faculty & research alumni recruiters & companies news about the gsb behavioral lab home people affiliated faculty phd students research participate for our researchers links contact us related sites request lab help reserve lab rooms email print share this image changes when you point at it behavioral lab the gsb's center for psychological research the behavioral lab is an interdisciplinary laboratory designed for the study of human subjects a major resource of the gsb the lab is available for use by all stanford gsb faculty and phd students and research is primarily conducted in the organizational behavior and behavioral marketing fields topics studied in the lab include decision making social justice stereotyping attitude formation and change negotiation team performance leadership power and morality the interdisciplinary nature of the lab means that it collaborates extensively with other departments on the stanford campus and through collaborations with our faculty and students works with outside research institutions the lab is staffed by a laboratory manager and three full time research assistants participate in research earn money the behavioral lab runs paid experimental studies both in the lab and online click here to sign up admissions faculty & research alumni recruiters & companies giving executive education news about the gsb copyright 2012 stanford graduate school of business site help terms of use & policies stanford university
